item.description:
Clockwork - K'nex Ball Machine
This is Clockwork, my fifth major K'nex ball machine, and my largest and most complex K'nex structure to date. It took 8 months to build, has over 40,000 pieces, over 450 feet of track, 21 different paths, 8 motors, 5 lifts, and a one-of-a-kind computer-controlled crane, as well as two computer-controlled illuminated K'nex balls. As requested, here is a raw video of the machine with the original sound: http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=pk8dr5IUMFs Also, a video of the machine running at night with the LED balls: http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=gY9BSh8aVQM EDIT: Since people have been asking about the music, it is an original composition I wrote specifically for this machine and this video.
